Objective :

Objective: Check Gaming products BIOS setup quick setting page information and function.
Trigger propose: To make sure BIOS setup quick setting page information and function is OK.
TC execute condition: Must execution during each BIOS formal release. This case is for Gaming products

1.Update case for Lenovo BIOS Setup Design Guide V3.7

Section : Prepare (60) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Flash the latest BIOS/EC/Preload.
Note: please check USB mouse/touchpad/touchpanel function when switch tab and change settings in Quick Setting page if project support
 
Section : Quick Setting Page check (180) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Power on system and press F2 immediately.
System will enter BIOS SETUP quick setting page.
>Background
Check background picture.
Background picture is full screen size tiled depend on different project. Please confirm with project whether the picture shows right or not.
>Help

Check help message on the left bottom of this page.

System should show below help message:


Arrows
--Select Items


Enter
--OK


Esc
--Leave Bios


F2 During Boot
--BIOS Setup


F12 During Boot
--Boot Device


During Boot(From FY25 products, change icon to )


--Novo Menu
>Product Logo
Check product logo.
Normally show 'LEGION'. Some project maybe not, please confirm with project.
>Information and Version
Check Information and version content.
Ensure system show CPU/GPU/Bios Version/Lenovo SN.
Check all information.
Ensure all information show correctly.

>Thermal Mode
Check system Thermal Mode.
Ensure Thermal Mode setting is the same as windows setting.

Check Thermal mode icon.

Make sure the icon is round

> Overclocking


Note:If no Overclocking in quick page, please skip.

Hidden if not support OC function

CPU

Default setting is Off, hidden if not support CPU OC

GPU

Default setting is off, hidden if not support GPU OC

Memory

Default setting in Off, hidden if not support memory OC
>Boot Device
Check boot device option.
Ensure system show all bootable devices.

>Legion Optimization

Check Legion Optimization settings

Ensure Legion Optimization setting can be changed.

>Graphic Device

Hidden if only one VGA, project dependent.

Check graphic device option.

For project support discrete graphic and support DDS, graphic device option should show 'Dynamic Graphics' and 'Discrete Graphics' and 'Integrated Graphics'.


For project support discrete graphic and not support DDS, graphic device option should show 'Discrete Graphics' and 'Switchable Graphics' and 'Integrated Graphics'.


Make sure show the same options with BIOS setup normal page -> Configuration -> Graphics Device
>More Settings
Select More settings button via touchpad/arrow/touchpanel(if supported).
System will switch to normal BIOS SETUP settings.

Check Background/Back Button or HOME button/Logo on BIOS SETUP normal page.


Note: Follow Setup design guide V3.8, change 'back' bitton to 'HOME' button.

Background: Background picture is full screen size tiled depend on different project.Please confirm with project whether the picture shows right or not.


Back Button or HOME button: System return to quick setting page.


Logo: Normally show 'LEGION'. Some project maybe not, please confirm with project.
>Exit
Select Exit button via touchpad/arrow/touchpanel(if supported).
System will exit BIOS SETUP and enter OS.
Go to BIOS setup normal page, change language setting to 'ä¸­æ–‡'.
Ensure all information show correctly.
 
Section : Thermal mode function check (90) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

Boot to Windows, change Thermal mode via:


1. Lenovo Vantage


2. Legion Zone


3. Fn+Q
Go to BIOS SETUP quick setting page, check Thermal mode.
Ensure the Thermal mode show the same as Windows.
Go to BIOS setup normal page, change language setting to 'ä¸­æ–‡'.
Ensure all information show correctly and function is OK.
 
Section : OC function check (120) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

Note:


1.skip if project not support OC function.


2.If no Overclocking in quick page, please skip this section.

Boot system to BIOS quick setting page, check OC item default setting.

Ensure all OC items default setting is off

Go to BIOS normal page, check OC item setting.

Ensure all OC item setting show Disabled.

Enable OC function, Save and exit.

Change to BIOS setup quick setting page, save and exit. Plug in AC adapter to system and go to Legion zone/Lenovo Vantage to check OC status.

For Legion Zone:


When change Thermal Mode, Legion zone will not prompt information.


 


For Lenovo Vantage:


When change to Balance/Performance mode, Lenovo Vantage will show "Overclock on" in Legion Edge-> Thermal mode


When change to Quiet mode, Lenovo Vantage will show nothing Legion Edge-> Thermal mode

Switch thermal mode under OS, check prompt message in Legion zone/Lenovo Vantage.

Remove AC adapter, check prompt message in Legion zone/Lenovo Vantage.

For Legion Zone:


When change to Balance/Performance mode, OC button will show turn off and gray out.


When change to Quiet mode, OC button will be hidden.


 


For Lenovo Vantage: Lenovo Vantage will show nothing Legion Edge-> Thermal mode
Enter BIOS quick setting page again, disable all OC items, go to BIOS normal page, ensure all OC related item setting should show disabled. Save and exit, then check PCM/Lenovo Vantage prompt message.
Ensure system show nothing in PCM/Lenovo Vantage.
Plug in AC adapter, check prompt message.
Ensure system show nothing in PCM/Lenovo Vantage.
> GPU OC
Skip if not support
Enable GPU OC in BIOS setup quick setting page, save and exit. Then plug in AC adapter under OS.
Open GPU Monitor and run Furmark for 10 mins, log GPU and VRAM frquency in Performance/Balance/Quiet mode.
System no hang, BSOD and etc.
Disable GPU OC in BIOS setup quick setting page, save and exit. Then plug in AC adapter under OS.
Open GPU Monitor and run Furmark for 10 mins, log GPU and VRAM frquency in Performance/Balance/Quiet mode.
System no hang, BSOD and etc.
Compare the GPU frequency when GPU enabled/disabled.
GPU OC enable frequency should be higher than GPU OC disabled on Performance and Balance mode.
Change to another Graphics Device setting and repeat above steps if project support.
> CPU OC
Skip if not support
Enable CPU OC in BIOS setup quick setting page, save and exit. Then plug in AC adapter under OS.
Run XTU/AVT to get CPU max frequency in Performance/Balance/Quiet mode.
CPU OC only can work on supported mode. Ensure all three mode CPU frequency meet spec.
Disable CPU OC in BIOS setup quick setting page, save and exit. Then plug in AC adapter under OS.
Run XTU/AVT to get CPU max frequency in Performance/Balance/Quiet mode.
Ensure CPU OC have no function in these three mode and CPU frequency meet spec.
>Memory OC
Skip if not support
Enable Memory OC in BIOS setup quick setting page, save and exit. Then plug in AC adapter under OS.
Go to Task Manager and switch to performance tab, check memory speed(AWF) in Performance/Balance/Quiet mode.
Ensure memory speed(AWF) = MRF on memory OC supported mode, memory speed(AWF) = BF on not supported mode.
Disable Memory OC in BIOS setup quick setting page, save and exit. Then plug in AC adapter under OS.
Go to Task Manager and switch to performance tab, check memory speed(AWF) in Performance/Balance/Quiet mode.
Ensure memory speed(AWF) = BF in these three mode.
Go to BIOS setup normal page, change language setting to 'ä¸­æ–‡'.
Ensure all information show correctly and function is OK.
 
Section : Boot Device function check (90) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Connect U disk, USB HDD, ODD and internal HDD to system.
Power on system and press F2 immediately.
System will enter BIOS setup quick setting page.
Check Boot Device list.
Ensure all bootable devices shown in Boot Device.
Change boot sequence, like ODD, U disk, USB HDD, internal HDD.
Go to BIOS SETUP normal page, check boot sequence in EFI -> Boot.
Ensure boot sequence show the same with BIOS setup quick setting page.
Back to BIOS SETUP quick setting page, save and exit.
Ensure system boot into corresponding device.
Select to Legacy, then repeat above steps. (skip if BIOS not support legacy boot)
Ensure function works normally.
Go to BIOS setup normal page, change language setting to 'ä¸­æ–‡'.
Ensure all information show correctly and function is OK.
 
Section : Graphic Device function check (90) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

Note: if system is UMA configuration, only need to enter OS to check Display adapter in Device Manager.

System only show Integrated graphic and driver is installed.
Power on system and enter OS.
Check Display adapters in Device Manager.
Ensure all graphic device drivers installed and no yellow bang
Reboot to BIOS SETUP quick setting page.

Check graphic device option.


Note:For A+A or A+N project, When choose Discrete Graphics, system will install all graphic device drivers

For system support DDS:


Dynamic Graphics


Discrete Graphics


For system not support DDS:


Discrete Graphics


Switchable Graphics


 


Please confirm with project for default setting.


When choose Discrete Graphics, system only install discrete graphic device driver; when choose Dynamic Graphics/Switchable Graphics, system will install all graphic device drivers
Go to BIOS SETUP normal page, check Graphics Device in Configuration.
Ensure Graphics Device show the same with quick setting page.
Back to BIOS SETUP quick setting page.
Save and exit, enter OS, check Display adapters in Device Manager.
Ensure all graphic device drivers are installed and no yellow bang.
Reboot to BIOS SETUP quick setting page again, change Graphics Device to non-default setting.
Go to BIOS SETUP normal page, check Graphics Device in Configuration.
Ensure Graphics Device show the same with quick setting page.
Back to BIOS SETUP quick setting page, save and exit.
Ensure system enter OS nornally.
Check Display adapters in Device Manager.
Ensure all graphic device drivers installed and no yellow bang.
Go to BIOS setup normal page, change language setting to 'ä¸­æ–‡'.
Ensure all information show correctly and function is OK.
 
Section : Exit (180) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Enter BIOS SETUP quick setting page.

Do not change any setting,


1. Select Exit button via touchpad/arrow/touchpanel(if supported).


2. Press Esc button.

Ensure system boot to OS directly.
Enter BIOS SETUP quick setting page again.

Change some option's value to non-default setting, then select Exit button/ press Esc button.

Ensure system will prompt below message:


Save your change ?


SAVE & EXIT


DISCARD CHANGE & EXIT


CANCEL
Select CANCEL/ press Esc.
Exit the setup confirmation.
Select Exit button/ press Esc again, choose SAVE & EXIT. System will reboot, enter BIOS SETUP quick setting page again.
System reboot normally, all option keep the changed value.

Change some option's value to non-default setting, select Exit button/ press Esc button.

Ensure system will prompt below message:


Save your change ?


SAVE & EXIT


DISCARD CHANGE & EXIT


CANCEL
Choose DISCARD CHANGE & EXIT. System will reboot, enter BIOS SETUP quick setting page again.
System reboot normally, the option's value is not changed.
Go to BIOS setup normal page, change language setting to 'ä¸­æ–‡'.
Ensure all information show correctly and function is OK.
 
Section : Settings changed in normal BIOS SETUP page (60) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Enter BIOS SETUP normal page.
Change Graphic Device setting in Configuration.
Go back to BIOS SETUP quick setting page, check Graphic Device setting.
Ensure the Graphic Device setting also changed.
Save and exit. Check graphic devices in DM.
Ensure graphic devices show correctly in DM.
Repeat above steps when change boot sequence in EFI -> Boot.
Ensure the boot sequence also changed.
Go to BIOS setup normal page, change language setting to 'ä¸­æ–‡'.
Ensure all information show correctly and function is OK.
